snippet.textDisplay:
Love and adore everything in this song so much. Here's my humble  interpretation of the song because I can't stop thinking on how many levels it speaks to us. I absolutely love the hedonistic absurdist approach taken by the songwriter. Gaddi being the metaphor of life tells how its gonna be like a journey, where purpose is to achieve happiness and making big sacrifices for that. While being a constant change, when you get a chance to process all of it, it is still a question for us that what meaning does it hold. But imagining sysiphus happy we move on from that question and keep going while enjoying whatever it throws in our way.
I like the interpretation of Gaddi as a person who's very confident, has an acheieved sense of identity and self, and may have self-actualized (which i gathered from Hassan Raheem's verses). 
I find it very spiritual in a way that it tells a story of becoming one with a higher self when Shazia Manzoor said "jhoom k chali sohne yaar di gali". It could be representing death and happily embracing the reunion with the higher being.
What i personally found so catching about the song is it is relatable to me as a person who has been constantly moving countries and cities for something better or finding happiness while being confident and stubborn about it. When the lyrics said " kithe khulla aasman kithe band gaaliyan" it takes me back to my hometown which is like a countryside and the freedom and fresh air I had there. Living in a metropolis for "khushyan kamaan lai" hit me hard.
